While this is just humor, and funny at times, US education has become a loser. Pew Research says that US education ranks about 24th in the world in Reading and Science and about 39th in math. Yes, yes, I know there are many fine teachers in the US who want to do the right thing. But it is time for these teachers and us to begin complaining on why huge taxes and huge amounts of money has yielded us a losing education system. I do not blame the teachers. I blame the Teachers Union who has gone political for this problem. As for those people who think all unions are wonderful, I give you the words of Eric Hoffer: ( by the way, I believed the idea he expresses long before I heard of his quote).

"Every great cause begins as a movement, becomes a business, and eventually degenerates into a racket." - Eric Hoffer

American Greatness 
By Eric Lendrum
March 21, 2023 ()

Philadelphia Reaches $9.25M Settlement with Anti-Police Rioters

On Monday, the city of Philadelphia agreed to pay $9.25 million to over 200 rioters who claimed to have been injured by police during the Black Lives Matter riots of 2020.

As reported by Fox News, the settlement was announced by the law firm Mincey Fitzpatrick Ross, LLC, which represented the 237 activists who participated in the riots between May 31st and June 1st, 2020, following the fentanyl overdose death of George Floyd.

In addition to the financial compensation, the city has also agreed to stop participating in a federal program that provides the police department with extra military equipment. The city will also pay about $500,000 for counseling services
